# Project Pages Conventions

## Stack

- **Next.js 16** (App Router) · **React 19** · **TypeScript** (strict) · **Supabase** (Postgres + Auth)
- Tailwind CSS 4 imported but barely used — components use **inline styles** exclusively
- Font: **Inter** via `next/font/google`, exposed as `--font-inter`
- Path alias: `@/*` → `./src/*`

## Directory Layout

```
src/
  app/            # Pages + API routes (App Router)
    api/
      projects/   # CRUD + reorder sub-routes
      tasks/      # CRUD per task
  components/     # Client components (ProjectCard, TaskRow, AddTaskForm, StatsPanel, AuthForm)
  hooks/          # useProjects — single data hook for all project/task state
  lib/supabase/   # client.ts (browser singleton) + server.ts (per-request with access token)
  types/          # index.ts — Task, Project, TaskColor, COLOR_OPTIONS, getColor()
supabase/
  migrations/     # Raw SQL migration files
```

## UI Design System

This app is **minimal, monochromatic, and warm**. Follow these values exactly.

### Colors

| Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|-------|
| Background | `#fafaf8` | Page background |
| Surface | `#fff` | Cards, nav bar, modals |
| Primary text | `#222` | Headings, active UI, progress bars, primary buttons |
| Body text | `#444` | Task titles (incomplete) |
| Muted text | `#888` · `#999` · `#aaa` · `#bbb` | Secondary labels, counters, placeholders — use lighter values for less importance |
| Completed text | `#bbb` | Struck-through task titles |
| Border | `#ebebeb` | Card/nav borders |
| Input border | `#e0e0e0` | Form fields |
| Divider | `#f0f0f0` | Task row separators, progress bar tracks |
| Active pill | `#222` bg + `#fff` text | Selected tab/button (dark on light inversion) |
| Error text | `#c0392b` | Form validation errors |

### Spacing & Radii

- Card padding: `20px`
- Card border-radius: `14px`
- Button/input border-radius: `8px`
- Card shadow: `0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.06)`
- Stat card shadow: `0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.04)`

### Typography

- Font family: `var(--font-inter), 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif`
- All font sizes: 11–17px (never larger outside of stat numbers at 28px)
- Weights: 400 (body), 500 (medium labels), 600 (buttons, emphasis), 700 (headings, card titles)
- Section headers: 12px, uppercase, `letter-spacing: 0.05em`, color `#aaa`, weight 500–600

### Interactive Patterns

- Progress bars: `#222` fill on `#f0f0f0` track, `transition: width 0.3s–0.4s`
- Buttons: no outline/border by default — use `background` + `color` contrast
- Hover actions (trash, checkbox): hidden by default, revealed via `.task-row:hover .task-actions` CSS
- Dashed borders for "add" affordances: `1.5px dashed #e0e0e0` or `#ddd`
- Color labels: use `COLOR_OPTIONS` from `@/types` — never introduce new colors

## Code Patterns

### Components

- Every component file starts with `"use client"`
- Functional components only — no class components
- Props defined via `interface` directly above the component
- Styles are **always inline** (`style={{…}}`), never CSS modules or Tailwind utility classes
- Global CSS (`globals.css`) is only for responsive breakpoints and pseudo-class styles that inline styles can't express (`:hover`, media queries)
- Icons are inline `<svg>` — no icon library

### State Management

- All project/task data flows through `useProjects()` hook
- Optimistic updates: local state is updated immediately after a successful API call, no re-fetch
- `useCallback` for all data mutation functions, `useMemo` for derived computations

### API Routes

- Auth: every route reads `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header, returns 401 if missing
- Server Supabase client: `createServerSupabaseClient(token)` creates a fresh client per request
- Error responses: `{ error: string }` with appropriate HTTP status
- Success responses: `{ data: … }`, `{ projects: … }`, or `{ ok: true }`
- Allowed update fields are explicitly whitelisted

### Data Model

- Tasks have `position` (integer) for drag-and-drop ordering and `completed` (boolean)
- Tasks ordered by `position ASC, created_at ASC` from the API
- Completed tasks are rendered at the bottom of each project card, capped at 5 visible with expand/collapse
- Projects have an `archived` boolean; archived projects are shown separately

## Important Constraints

- **This app is in production** — never break existing functionality when making changes
- No external UI libraries (no shadcn, MUI, Chakra, etc.)
- No new dependencies without explicit approval
- Keep the visual language consistent: if it doesn't match the existing monochrome+warm palette, don't add it
